<TITLE> Bangladesh SAFF Women's Handball Championship runners-up </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 26 (bdnews24.com) - Bangladesh became runners-up in the third SAFF Women's Handball Championship after losing to hosts India in the final in Lucknow, India. Bangladesh conceded a 29-15 defeat to India after trailing by 14-6 in the first half on Sunday. Shila and Mayna scored five and four goals for Bangladesh, who received Rs 20,000 as prize money. Pakistan finished third beating Nepal in the four-nation tournament. The executive committee of South Asian Handball Federation decided to organise SAFF Men's Beach Handball in Faisalabad in Pakistan from June 27 to 29. The meeting also decided to organise the third SAFF Men's Handball Championship in Ludhiana in India in the last week of December, said a press release from Bangladesh Handball Federation Monday. 
